tion  which may arise  Instead  we hope to help you think safe  in your everyday life  The suggestions presented here are examples of common sense behavior that we hope will help you to make life safer and more secure  Personal Safety Awareness Though it is hard to think about  summer is over and cadets have returned to school  Hundreds of young adults have arrived from all over the county  either for the first time  or to embark on another semester  While the new semester brings opportunities and excitement  there is still the potential to be a victim of crime  Below are some tips for young adults while they are spending time both on and off Post  Use the buddy system  Don t walk alone if possible  especially at night  Report any suspicious activity observed on Post to the VMI Police or Lexington Police  It may turn out to be nothing  but why risk it  Stay in well lighted areas while walking at night  and entering and exiting buildings  If an area feels unsafe  chances are that others feel the same way  Inform the police and let them help make things safer on your Post  Be alert to what goes on around Post  The email notifications of criminal activity around Post may seem annoying  but being aware of what is going on out there is the first step in making sure that you don t get caught in the middle of it  Use good judgment when consuming alcohol  Remember that excessive drinking can lower your inhibitions and affect your judgment  increasing the risk of injury or victimization      Safety and Security Tips Crime prevention means being aware of your environment and remaining alert to situations that could make you vulnerable to crime VMI Police Department cannot give you a list specific measures that will protect you from every threatening situation  which may arise  Instead  we hope to help you think safe  in your everyday life  The suggestions presented here are examples of common sense behavior that we hope will help you to make life safer and more secure  Person